README for dracut

REQUIREMENTS

    For encrypted root need the following:
    --------------------------------------

    1. Install cryptsetup

    2. In kernel configuration is recommended to include the following
       necessary features 'statically', i.e. not as modules.

       General Setup --->
         [*] Initial RAM filesystem and RAM disk (iniramfs/initrd) support

       Device Drivers --->
         Multiple devices driver support (RAID and LVM) --->
           [*] Device mapper support
           [*] Crypt target support
    
       Note: you also have to include the desired

         Block modes
         Hash modes
         Digest
         Ciphers

       in Cryptographic API --->

       to be able to decrypt your partitions later.


POST-INSTALL

    Generate an init ramdisk:

        dracut -q --kver 5.2.17 /boot/initrd-5.2.17.img

    Install grub2 into the ESP:

        grub-install --efi-directory=/boot --recheck

    Generate a grub2 configuration file:

        grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg

